<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
Male with almost triangular patch of light brown stiff bristles on S4 and emarginate apicomedial area of S5 surrounded by dense branched hairs, lateral corners of S5 protruding. Female paraclypeal and supraclypeal marks present, tibial scopa ochre, T2 with a few black hairs anteriorly, process on S6 large narrow, posteriorly with angular smooth ridge Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Amegilla (Asaropoda) albigenella Michener, 1965." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.908.47375.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/376121" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">4L</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
